# Non-interactive mode: allowlist prompt fallback

In some environments, terminal commands may be blocked by an allowlist/approval gate, which can stall unattended work.

## Rule (guardrail)

- Prefer workspace edits over shell-based file writes when allowlisting would block progress.
- Use `docker exec` only when unavoidable.

## Runbook

See `noninteractive-allowlist-fallback` skill.
